OpenVPN Setup & IP Verification (Linux)
Connect to VPNBook France server and verify IP change with curl ifconfig.me.

Check Original IP
bash
curl ifconfig.me
# Note your real IP address
Install OpenVPN
bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openvpn -y
Download & Connect VPN
bash
cd Downloads
ls
# vpnbook-openvpn-fr200

cd vpnbook-openvpn-fr200
ls
# vpnbook-fr200-tcp80.ovpn

sudo openvpn vpnbook-fr200-tcp80.ovpn
Credentials:

text
Username: vpnbook
Password: [Get from vpnbook.com via Firefox]
Verify VPN Connection
Open NEW terminal (don't close VPN):

bash
curl ifconfig.me
# Should show France IP now!
Quick Commands Summary
bash
# Before VPN
curl ifconfig.me                    # Real IP

# Install
sudo apt update && sudo apt install openvpn -y

# Connect (VPNBook France TCP80)
cd ~/Downloads/vpnbook-openvpn-fr200
sudo openvpn vpnbook-fr200-tcp80.ovpn  # vpnbook / [password]

# After VPN (new terminal)
curl ifconfig.me                    # France IP âœ…
Expected Results
Step	Command	Result
Before	curl ifconfig.me	Your real IP
After VPN	curl ifconfig.me	French IP (different!)
Disconnect VPN
bash
# Press Ctrl+C in VPN terminal
# Or kill process: pkill openvpn
